subject: [OT] Ant 1.6 (was Re: Junit target not being executed by Ant)
msgSnippet: ... The manual is part of the nightly builds (which are created from HEAD). A very short (and probably incomplete) list of new features is part of WHATSNEW,
messageBody:
On Mon, 04 Aug 2003, billy bacon <billy.bacon@...> wrote:

> Is there an api or manual for the Ant 1.6 alpah version
> that would explain the spawn attribute and any other
> new features?

The manual is part of the nightly builds (which are created from
HEAD).

A very short (and probably incomplete) list of new features is part of
WHATSNEW, see
<http://cvs.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/ant/WHATSNEW?rev=HEAD>.

Stefan
